      "description": "Jordison retained his Paiste RUDE and 2002 cymbal setup for *Vol. 3*, but the production environment transformed how these instruments appear on the record. Under Rick Rubin and Greg Fidelman at Henson Studios, the RUDE cymbals' raw, unlathed character comes through with definition that Iowa's compressed production rarely provided.\n\nThe 2002 Power Ride plays a more prominent role on Vol. 3 than on Iowa — the album's wider range of tempos and the presence of compositionally significant riding patterns meant that Rubin's production preserved ride cymbal work as a melodic and textural element. Tracks like \"The Nameless\" and \"Vermilion\" feature ride patterns that Iowa's wall-of-noise approach would have buried.\n\nThe crash array (16\"–19\") provided the same dynamic hierarchy as the Iowa setup, but individual cymbal character is audible in Rubin's mix. Jordison's selective use of different crash sizes — a technique present on Iowa but imperceptible in that production — is clearly differentiated on Vol. 3.\n\nThe dual China cymbals (20\" and 22\") continued as Slipknot's signature percussive punctuation. On \"Pulse of the Maggots\" and \"The Blister Exists,\" the China accents define the arrangement's climax points with more tonal specificity than Iowa's production allowed.",
