      "description": "Joey Jordison's primary kit for *All Hope Is Gone* was a Pearl Reference Series — Pearl's flagship multi-species shell line, engineered to combine the warmth of maple with the attack and high-end definition of birch. The Reference shells use strategically placed maple and birch plies designed to optimise each drum's tonal character: birch in positions that emphasise attack and brightness, maple in positions that deepen the fundamental note. For a drummer who had built his career on a Pearl Masterworks Custom maple/mahogany hybrid, the move to Reference represented a refinement of the same philosophy: hybrid shells engineered for a specific sonic outcome.\n\nThe double 22\" x 18\" bass drums remained the Slipknot standard — but Dave Fortman's production approach at Sound Farm gave them a more defined, less compressed character than the Iowa sessions. The kicks on \"Psychosocial\" and \"Gematria\" sit forward in the mix with clear attack and substantial low-end body, the result of a careful blend of triggered consistency and the natural resonance of the Reference's larger shells.\n\nThe tom configuration for *All Hope Is Gone* was more compact than the expanded five-rack-tom setup of Vol. 3 — two rack toms (10\", 12\") plus two floor toms (14\", 16\") — reflecting the album's tighter, more song-focused arrangements. Joey's fills across the record orchestrate around this tighter spread with a melodic clarity that the wider Vol. 3 configuration sometimes obscured. The Black/Red finish gave the kit a visual identity matching the album's darker, more cohesive aesthetic — distinct from the custom purple of Iowa and the more neutral finishes of Vol. 3.\n\nThe Reference Series was a recurring choice across Joey's late-Slipknot era and his work with Murderdolls and other projects of the period. *All Hope Is Gone* captures the kit at the peak of its development as Joey's primary studio voice.",
